column5: It's Saturday, May 17th at 4:00 a.m.. We are on our way to Armstrong for another fly in starting tomorrow. WOW! This winter seems to have gone by quickly for me for some reason. Thanks to everybody for all the advise and conversation throughout the winter.AL
Go get-em Al!!! My Dad and I have to wait 19 more weeks before we're "on our way".
its 2 weeks from 2 days ago for us. taking our boat for the first time.
2 months from today. can't wait. good luck.
95 hours and 53 minutes...tick...tock...tick...tock...Good luck to all and report your results back on this board. - Rick
That would be 40 days and 3 hours from now that we'll be pulling away from the dock.or ... 963 hoursor ... 57780 minutesor ... 3466800 seconds - but who's counting anyway?
48 HOURS FROM RIGHT NOW. BERRONS RIVER, NORTH OF RED LAKE.
Going on a Fly-In out of Armstrong on June 8th to 15th. Have a blast and when you get back e-mail me at [email protected] how you did.Thanks Larry S
